logicalColumns.name: Due Date
logicalColumns.description: This column provides the effective Due Date for a Line Item on the PO. If the line has a Promise Date, this date is used as the Due Date. If there is no Promise Date, the Need By Date is used instead.

expressionObjects: logicalColumn:EBS.PO Purchase Orders Fact.Need By Date

logicalColumns.name: Late Shipment Flag
logicalColumns.description: This column determines if a PO Shipment was recieved after the due date. If the Shipment Closed Date is > Due Date, the flag = 'Y'. If the Shipment Closed Date =< Due Date, then the flag = 'N'.

logicalExpression.expressionTemplate: CASE  WHEN  TIMESTAMPDIFF( SQL_TSI_DAY , %1,  IFNULL(%2,  CURRENT_DATE )) = 0 THEN 'N' WHEN  TIMESTAMPDIFF( SQL_TSI_DAY , %1,  IFNULL(%3,  CURRENT_DATE )) < 0 THEN 'N' ELSE 'Y' END

logicalColumns.name: Days Past Due
logicalColumns.description: This column calculates the number of days between the Due Date and the Shipment Closed Date. If there is no Shipment Closed Date, the Current Date is used. Negative results signify the number of days until the Due Date, while positive results show the number of days past the Due Date.

expressionObjects: logicalColumn:EBS.PO Purchase Orders Fact.Need By Date

logicalColumns.name: Business Days Past Due
logicalColumns.description: This is an approximation of how many Business Days the PO Shipment was recieved from the Promised or Need By Date. This is achieved by multiplying the standard Days Past Due logic by 5/7.

expressionObjects: logicalColumn:EBS.PO Purchase Orders Fact.Need By Date

logicalColumns.name: Early Within Tolerance
logicalColumns.description: This flag determines whether or not a PO Shipment was recieved within early delivery tolerance level of 5 days.  Y = Within Tolerance, N = Out of Tolerance. This calculation does not determine if the shipment was late if it is out of tolerance.

logicalExpression.expressionTemplate: CASE  WHEN  TIMESTAMPDIFF( SQL_TSI_DAY , %1, %2) IN (0, 1, 2, 3, 4) THEN 'Y' ELSE 'N' END

logicalColumns.name: Count of POs Currently Past Due

logicalExpression.expressionTemplate: FILTER( COUNT(DISTINCT %1) USING  CASE  WHEN %2 <  CURRENT_DATE  AND %3 < %4 THEN 'Y' ELSE 'N' END  = 'Y')
expressionObjects: logicalColumn:EBS.PO Purchase Orders Fact.PO Header Id
logicalColumn:EBS.PO Purchase Orders Fact.PO Received Quantity

logicalColumns.name: Last Approved Date
logicalColumns.description: This is the most recent Header Approval Date

logicalColumns.name: PO Quantity
logicalColumns.description: To be used in the Count of PO Currently Past Due column. Aggregated columns are not allowed in a FILTER function, thus necessitating an attribute column of the amount. Not to be migrated into the Presentation layer.

filter.expressionTemplate: CAST (%1 AS CHARACTER ( 30 )) =  VALUEOF(NQ_SESSION.%2) OR  VALUEOF(NQ_SESSION.%2) = 'ALL'
